description:
&lt;p&gt;The East of England Ambulance Trust has a vacancy for the position of Clinical Practice Supervisor to join us in an emergent role within the People and Culture Directorate. This is an exciting time to join the Trust, as we are now moving towards a holistic education and development methodology for our existing staff and future workforce. Please note, this position provides specific 12-month secondment cover for the Bedfordshire, Hertfordshire and West Essex system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced clinician, leader and educator, who is passionate about improving our service and processes – both capability and quality. The successful candidate will take the lead for facilitating and developing learning for all grades of staff and students across all pathways, with primary focus on the operational environment. They will promote high quality care, clinical expertise, and evidence-based practice to meet the needs of our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will be the key liaison with learners, our university partners, education and training team, and operational teams across the region. The role also provides expert support in relation to higher education, clinical practice, and professional pathways. This includes the provision of appropriate mentorship, supervision, and support for all operational staff and both internal and external students, and act as a quality assurance mechanism for both practice educators and learners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will require travel, autonomy, and close liaison with partners across the Trust in support of the greater organisational objectives. As a management position there may also be line management expectations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBenjamin HaselwoodJob titleHigher Education and Clinical Practice LeadEmail addressbenjamin.haselwood@eastamb.nhs.ukTelephone number07522215758&lt;/p&gt;
